<subSubSection id="6EDC654FFE46FF8DFF0AFE2E5D32FC6D" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph id="267936C4FE46FF8DFF0AFE2E5CB8FDED" blockId="6.[166,1225,479,986]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Very widespread, North Europe: 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFC8FFE115F90FE4E" box="[862,982,479,505]" name="Denmark" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Denmark</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFC3BFE11580DFE4E" box="[1002,1099,479,505]" name="Sweden" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Sweden</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFB8EFE2E5885FE4D" box="[1119,1219,480,506]" name="Norway" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Norway</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFF77FE315D52FDAE" box="[166,276,511,537]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Scotland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFEF1FE315D3AFDAE" box="[288,380,511,537]" name="Ireland" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Ireland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFE59FE315DAEFDAE" box="[392,488,511,537]" name="Finland" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Finland</collectingCountry>
to Siberia. South Europe: 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFCF6FE315F27FDAE" box="[807,865,511,537]" name="Italy" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Italy</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFCBCFE315FF3FDAE" box="[877,949,511,537]" name="Spain" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Spain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFC11FDCE585EFDAD" box="[960,1048,512,538]" name="France" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">France</collectingCountry>
. North Africa. Middle East: 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFE9DFDD15DEEFD8E" box="[332,424,543,569]" name="Turkey" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFE67FDEE5DA8FD8D" box="[438,494,544,570]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Iran</collectingCountry>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE46FF8DFE2AFDD15E89FD8D" author="Rozkosny, R." box="[507,719,543,570]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 100" refId="ref6810" refString="Rozkosny, R. 1987. A review of the Palaearctic Sciomyzidae (Diptera). Biologia 86. Prirodovedecka Fakulta, Univerzita J. E. Purkyne, Brne, 1 - 100." type="book chapter" year="1987">Rozkošný (1987)</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE46FF8DFD0CFDD15CBCFDED" author="Seddighi Sadr, F. &amp; Mohammadzade Namin, S." pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="43 - 45" refId="ref6894" refString="Seddighi Sadr, F., Mohammadzade Namin, S. 2016. The snail killing flies (Diptera, Sciomyzidae) in Gilan Province, with a new record for Iranian fauna. Ukrainska Entomofaunistyka, 7 (1), 43 - 45." type="journal article" year="2016">Seddighi Sadr, Mohammadzade Namin (2016)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE46FF8DFF0AFD915D32FC6D" blockId="6.[166,1225,479,986]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
Biology. The complete life cycle has been realized in laboratory by 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE46FF8DFBE6FD91588EFDCD" author="Vala, J. - C." box="[1079,1224,607,634]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="67 - 77" refId="ref7366" refString="Vala, J. - C. 1986. Description des stades larvaires et donnees sur la biologie et la phenologie de Trypetoptera punctulata (Diptera, Sciomyzidae). Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, 22 (1), 67 - 77." type="journal article" year="1986">Vala (1986)</bibRefCitation>
who described all the immature stages. If adult emerge from mid-April no matting is observed before August, due to a long pre-oviposition period, and flies are collected until early November (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE46FF8DFE6BFD715E04FD6D" author="Vala, J. - C." box="[442,578,703,730]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="67 - 77" refId="ref7366" refString="Vala, J. - C. 1986. Description des stades larvaires et donnees sur la biologie et la phenologie de Trypetoptera punctulata (Diptera, Sciomyzidae). Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, 22 (1), 67 - 77." type="journal article" year="1986">Vala, 1986</bibRefCitation>
). In laboratory, larvae attacked and fed the terrestrial gastropods 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE46FF8DFEEDFD115F51FD4D" authority="(Poiret, 1801)" baseAuthorityName="Poiret" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[316,791,735,762]" class="Gastropoda" family="Geomitridae" genus="Candidula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="unifasciata">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE46FF8DFEEDFD115E12FD4E" box="[316,596,735,761]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Candidula unifasciata</emphasis>
(Poiret, 1801)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE46FF8DFCFBFD2E5882FD4D" authority="(Muller, 1774)" baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[810,1220,735,762]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" genus="Cornu" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="aspersum">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE46FF8DFCFBFD2E5FBFFD4E" box="[810,1017,736,762]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Cornu aspersum</emphasis>
(Müller, 1774)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE46FF8DFF77FCCE5DD2FCAE" baseAuthorityName="Da Costa" baseAuthorityYear="1778" box="[166,404,767,793]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lauriidae" genus="Lauria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cylindracea">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE46FF8DFF77FCCE5DD2FCAE" box="[166,404,767,793]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Lauria cylindracea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingRegion id="E402F826FE46FF8DFE7AFD315DB0FCAE" box="[427,502,767,793]" country="New Zealand" name="West Coast" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Costa</collectingRegion>
, 1778) and 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE46FF8DFD4AFD315836FCAD" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[667,1136,767,794]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hygromiidae" genus="Trochulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hispidus">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE46FF8DFD4AFD315FCCFCAE" box="[667,906,767,793]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Trochulus hispidus</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE46FF8DFB56FD315CA5FC8E" author="Vala, J. - C." pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="67 - 77" refId="ref7366" refString="Vala, J. - C. 1986. Description des stades larvaires et donnees sur la biologie et la phenologie de Trypetoptera punctulata (Diptera, Sciomyzidae). Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, 22 (1), 67 - 77." type="journal article" year="1986">Vala, 1986</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE46FF8DFF22FCD15DFEFC8D" author="Gaponov, S. P." box="[243,440,799,826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="54 - 63" refId="ref6197" refString="Gaponov, S. P. 2016. Fauna and bioecology of snail-killing flies (Diptera: Sciomyzidae) in the central black soil region of Russia. Proceedings of Voronezh State University. Ser.: Chemistry. Biology. Pharmacy, 1, 54 - 63." type="journal article" year="2016">Gaponov, 2016</bibRefCitation>
). With the viviparous 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE46FF8DFD09FCEE5FC1FC8E" baseAuthorityName="Da Costa" baseAuthorityYear="1778" box="[728,903,799,825]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lauriidae" genus="Lauria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cylindracea">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE46FF8DFD09FCEE5FC1FC8E" box="[728,903,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">L. cylindracea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the first-instar larvae of 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE46FF8DFF77FC8E5D0BFCEE" baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[166,333,831,857]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Trypetoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctulata">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE46FF8DFF77FC8E5D0BFCEE" box="[166,333,831,857]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">T. punctulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fed firstly the young snails located in the pallial cavity of the mother host (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE46FF8DFF3AFC915D35FCCD" author="Vala, J. - C." box="[235,371,863,890]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="67 - 77" refId="ref7366" refString="Vala, J. - C. 1986. Description des stades larvaires et donnees sur la biologie et la phenologie de Trypetoptera punctulata (Diptera, Sciomyzidae). Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, 22 (1), 67 - 77." type="journal article" year="1986">Vala, 1986</bibRefCitation>
). Then, they fed the later before to leave the shell, and the second and third instar larvae attack larger snails (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE46FF8DFD58FCB15F55FC2D" author="Vala, J. - C." box="[649,787,895,922]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="67 - 77" refId="ref7366" refString="Vala, J. - C. 1986. Description des stades larvaires et donnees sur la biologie et la phenologie de Trypetoptera punctulata (Diptera, Sciomyzidae). Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, 22 (1), 67 - 77." type="journal article" year="1986">Vala, 1986</bibRefCitation>
). Puparia are mostly formed inside the host snail´s shell. The species is univoltine and overwintering as pupa (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE46FF8DFBEFFC515882FC0E" author="Vala, J. - C." box="[1086,1220,927,953]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="67 - 77" refId="ref7366" refString="Vala, J. - C. 1986. Description des stades larvaires et donnees sur la biologie et la phenologie de Trypetoptera punctulata (Diptera, Sciomyzidae). Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, 22 (1), 67 - 77." type="journal article" year="1986">Vala, 1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE46FF8DFF77FC715D2EFC6D" author="Gaponov, S. P." box="[166,360,959,986]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="54 - 63" refId="ref6197" refString="Gaponov, S. P. 2016. Fauna and bioecology of snail-killing flies (Diptera: Sciomyzidae) in the central black soil region of Russia. Proceedings of Voronezh State University. Ser.: Chemistry. Biology. Pharmacy, 1, 54 - 63." type="journal article" year="2016">Gaponov, 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6EDC654FFE46FF8DFF77FBEA588FF888" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" type="key">
<paragraph id="267936C4FE46FF8DFF77FBEA5847FBE3" blockId="6.[166,1112,1060,1108]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE46FF8DFF77FBEA5847FBE3" bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
Key to the 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE46FF8DFEC0FBEA5D92FB8D" box="[273,468,1060,1082]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE46FF8DFEC0FBEA5DCFFB8E" bold="true" box="[273,393,1060,1081]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Coremacera</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
occurring in Middle East and Central Asia (modified from 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE46FF8DFBF4FBEA5D74FBE3" author="Vala, J. - C. &amp; Leclercq, M." pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref7502" refString="Vala, J. - C., Leclercq, M. 1981. Taxonomie et repartition geographique des especes du genre Coremacera Rondani, 1856, Sciomyzidae (Diptera) palearctiques. Bulletin de l'institInst royal de Sciences Naturelles de Belgique, 53 (10), 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="1981">Vala, Leclercq,1981</bibRefCitation>
) (Distribution follows 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE46FF8DFDC9FBF05F46FBE3" author="Rozkosny, R. &amp; Elberg, K." box="[536,768,1086,1108]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="167 - 193" refId="ref6845" refString="Rozkosny, R., Elberg, K. 1984. Family Sciomyzidae (Tetanoceridae). In: Soos, A. and Papp, L., eds. Catalogue of Palaearctic Diptera. Vol. 9. Akademiai Kiado, Budapest, 167 - 193." type="book chapter" year="1984">Rozkošný, Elberg,1984</bibRefCitation>
); 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE46FF8DFCC1FBF15FBDFBE3" author="Leclercq, M. &amp; Schacht, W." box="[784,1019,1086,1108]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="57 - 63" refId="ref6577" refString="Leclercq, M., Schacht, W. 1986. The Sciomyzidae of Turkey (Diptera, Sciomyzidae). Entomofauna, 7 (4), 57 - 63." type="journal article" year="1986">Leclercq, Schacht, 1986</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE46FF8DFF77FBB8588FFB3B" blockId="6.[166,1225,1142,1855]" box="[166,1225,1142,1164]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">1. Face with a black round spot or black median strip below antenna. ..................................................... 2</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE46FF8DFF77FB5D588FFB1F" blockId="6.[166,1225,1142,1855]" box="[166,1225,1171,1192]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">— Face without black spots blow antenna. ................................................................................................ 4</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE46FF8DFF77FB7E588FFB55" blockId="6.[166,1225,1142,1855]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
2. Mainly black species; face with black median strip from base of antenna to the mouth edge (
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFBADFB7E5883FB72" box="[1148,1221,1200,1221]" name="Cyprus" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFF23FB035D7EFB55" box="[242,312,1229,1250]" name="Greece" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Greece</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFE93FB035DCAFB55" box="[322,396,1229,1250]" name="Turkey" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Turkey</collectingCountry>
). ...................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE46FF8DFC72FB03588FFB55" authority="(Loew 1845)" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[931,1225,1228,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Coremacera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscuripennis">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE46FF8DFC72FB035800FB56" box="[931,1094,1228,1250]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">C. obscuripennis</emphasis>
(Loew 1845)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE46FF8DFF77FB24588FFB48" blockId="6.[166,1225,1142,1855]" box="[166,1225,1258,1279]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">— Mainly brown species; face with a black round spots blow antenna. ................................................... 3</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE46FF8DFF77FAC9588FFAC5" blockId="6.[166,1225,1142,1855]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
3. Wing: costal margin brown with several light spots; base of wing to anterior cross vein yellow, without reticulate patterns; mesonotum with a longitudinal median yellow dusting strips surrounding with 2 longitudinal grey strips (Central Europe and 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFD60FA8E5E9CFAE2" box="[689,730,1344,1365]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFD35FA8E5F16FAE2" box="[740,848,1344,1365]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
, Armtnia, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFC64FA8E5FB9FAE2" box="[949,1023,1344,1365]" name="Turkey" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Turkey</collectingCountry>
). .............................. .......................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE46FF8DFC00FA93588FFAC5" authority="(Loew, 1847)" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[977,1225,1373,1394]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Coremacera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catenata">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE46FF8DFC00FA935806FAC5" box="[977,1088,1373,1394]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">C. catenata</emphasis>
(Loew, 1847)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE46FF8DFF77FAB4588FFA7F" blockId="6.[166,1225,1142,1855]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
— Wing: uniformly reticulated pattern with small spots; hind margin with narrow brownish band; mesonotum dark brown covered by grey dusting with black spots at the base of bristles (
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFBF4FA5958D1FA1B" box="[1061,1175,1431,1452]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
). ..... .................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE46FF8DFC75FA7D588FFA7F" authority="(Elberg, 1968)" baseAuthorityName="Elberg" baseAuthorityYear="1968" box="[932,1225,1459,1480]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Coremacera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turkestanica">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE46FF8DFC75FA7D5871FA7F" box="[932,1079,1459,1480]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">C. turkestanica</emphasis>
(Elberg, 1968)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE46FF8DFF77FA1E588FF9B5" blockId="6.[166,1225,1142,1855]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
4. Wing densely reticulate pattern, with a broad brown band from costal margin of wing to apex (Europe, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFF23FA235D7CF9B5" box="[242,314,1517,1538]" name="Turkey" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFE92FA235D28F9B5" box="[323,366,1517,1538]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Iran</collectingCountry>
). ........................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE46FF8DFC72FA23588FF9B5" authority="(Fabricius 1775)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[931,1225,1517,1538]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Coremacera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE46FF8DFC72FA235865F9B5" box="[931,1059,1517,1538]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">C. marginata</emphasis>
(Fabricius 1775)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE46FF8DFF77F9C4588FF9A8" blockId="6.[166,1225,1142,1855]" box="[166,1225,1546,1567]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">— Wing with normal reticulate pattern, costal margin of wing with whitish or brownish spots. ............. 5</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE46FF8DFF77F9E9588FF98B" blockId="6.[166,1225,1142,1855]" box="[166,1225,1575,1596]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">5. Wing with transverse brown bands. ........................................................................................................ 6</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE46FF8DFF77F98D588FF9C2" blockId="6.[166,1225,1142,1855]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
— Wing without transverse brown bands, with large light spots, apex of wing from R2+3 to M1+2 with a dark brown band (Eurasia, North and south Europe). .......................................... 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE46FF8DFC15F9AE588FF9C2" authority="Rozkosny, 1981" authorityName="Rozkosny" authorityYear="1981" box="[964,1225,1632,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Coremacera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fabricii">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE46FF8DFC15F9AE5861F9C2" box="[964,1063,1632,1653]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">C. fabricii</emphasis>
Rozkosny, 1981
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE46FF8DFF77F9B3588FF97B" blockId="6.[166,1225,1142,1855]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
7. Wings dark brown, apical half with 2 light transverse bands separated by a small brown transverse band; mesonotum brownish with grey and yellow dusting, many small black and brown spots arranged symmetrically; (Europe, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFE0FF9785E60F97B" box="[478,550,1718,1740]" name="Turkey" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Turkey</collectingCountry>
). ............................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE46FF8DFC09F978588FF97B" authority="(Loew, 1860)" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[984,1225,1718,1740]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Coremacera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trivittata">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE46FF8DFC09F9785801F97B" box="[984,1095,1718,1740]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">C. trivittata</emphasis>
(Loew, 1860)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE46FF8DFF77F91D588FF888" blockId="6.[166,1225,1142,1855]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
— Wings light brown, apical half with 2 rows of light spots separated by larger brown transverse bands; mesonotum light brown with whitish dusting, finely brown punctuated and 2 longitudinal rows of brown spots along the dorsocentral bristles and some small brown spots laterally (south Europe, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFB53F8C25880F895" box="[1154,1222,1804,1826]" name="Turkey" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE46FF8DFF23F8E75D58F888" box="[242,286,1833,1855]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Iran</collectingCountry>
). .............................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE46FF8DFC30F8E4588FF888" authority="(Loew, 1835)" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[993,1225,1833,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Coremacera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amoena">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE46FF8DFC30F8E45801F888" box="[993,1095,1834,1855]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">C. amoena</emphasis>
(Loew, 1835)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
